sql:
SELECT airline_name
FROM airlines
WHERE airline_id = '0';

SELECT AVG(average_dep_delay) AS avg_on_time_dep_delay
FROM flight_analysis
WHERE on_time_percentage = 100;

external_knowledge:
- "significat delays" refers to average departure delays exceeding 10 minutes; 
- "Wednesdays in October" narrows down the analysis to a specific weekday and month; 
- "more than 100 flights" ensures the analysis only includes airlines with a substantial number of flights during the specified time frame, providing a more reliable average delay measurement.
